currentDoc:
What Stereotypical Characters Make You Cringe?

What stereotypical characters in books, movies or television shows make you cringe and why? Would you ever not watch or read something because of its offensive portrayal of someone?

---

In my opinion,

currentSuggestions.original: I'm sure the writers of Married with Children knew it was offensive, but did they care at the time?
currentSuggestions.trimmed: I'm sure the writers of Married with Children knew it was offensive, but did they care at the time?

currentSuggestions.original: I'm brave enough to stand up for myself, but not all the people I love are.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: I'm brave enough to stand up for myself, but not all the people I love are.

currentSuggestions.original: I still think shows like Married with Children are funny, but that's because they deal with unrealistic and exaggerated stereotypes.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: I still think shows like Married with Children are funny, but that's because they deal with unrealistic and exaggerated stereotypes.

currentSuggestions.original: Instead of laughing, I began feeling uncomfortable and uncertain that I wanted to watch that program anymore.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: Instead of laughing, I began feeling uncomfortable and uncertain that I wanted to watch that program anymore.

currentSuggestions.original: That real people were hurt by that kind of humor.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: That real people were hurt by that kind of humor.

ops.insert: Instead of laughing, I began feeling uncomfortable and uncertain that I wanted to watch that program anymore.

currentSuggestions.original: What will be my tipping point for comedy?
currentSuggestions.trimmed: What will be my tipping point for comedy?

currentSuggestions.original: I wonder if at some point I'll stop laughing, and simply look away.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: I wonder if at some point I'll stop laughing, and simply look away.

currentSuggestions.original: It is certainly a change that has taken place in the last 10 or 15 years.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: It is certainly a change that has taken place in the last 10 or 15 years.

currentSuggestions.original: It'd be nice if there was a huge shift in things like that, that everyone became more sensitive to each other and how they interact with one another
currentSuggestions.trimmed: It'd be nice if there was a huge shift in things like that, that everyone became more sensitive to each other and how they interact with one another

currentSuggestions.original: I hope that doesn't happen.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: I hope that doesn't happen.

ops.insert: What will be my tipping point for comedy?

currentSuggestions.original: Learning comes at a price.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: Learning comes at a price.

currentSuggestions.original: I can't watch some shows any more because of that tipping point.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: I can't watch some shows any more because of that tipping point.

currentSuggestions.original: Some people can't learn, they don't have that tipping point - or they choose not to use that tipping point.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: Some people can't learn, they don't have that tipping point - or they choose not to use that tipping point.

currentSuggestions.original: The example that comes to mind is "cracking" on someone's weight.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: The example that comes to mind is "cracking" on someone's weight.

currentSuggestions.original: Sometimes, I'm not sure why my tipping point moves.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: Sometimes, I'm not sure why my tipping point moves.

ops.insert: The example that comes to mind is "cracking" on someone's weight.

currentSuggestions.original: It's really not about the people making the jokes, it's about how I've seen people struggle with weight over the years.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: It's really not about the people making the jokes, it's about how I've seen people struggle with weight over the years.

currentSuggestions.original: I don't think it's a proper subject for comedy.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: I don't think it's a proper subject for comedy.

currentSuggestions.original: I now see it as hurtful, and I really don't know how some people continue to laugh at that, because it no longer seems very funny
currentSuggestions.trimmed: I now see it as hurtful, and I really don't know how some people continue to laugh at that, because it no longer seems very funny

currentSuggestions.original: I see it as truly mean spirited.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: I see it as truly mean spirited.

currentSuggestions.original: It's just too close to home, and it hurts my feelings.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: It's just too close to home, and it hurts my feelings.

ops.insert: I now see it as hurtful, and I really don't know how some people continue to laugh at that, because it no longer seems very funny

currentSuggestions.original: But, from what I've seen about people in my life, its the same thing.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: But, from what I've seen about people in my life, its the same thing.

currentSuggestions.original: When I say that I never want to read or watch a fictional character do a stereotypical thing, it could be any of the reasons mentioned above.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: When I say that I never want to read or watch a fictional character do a stereotypical thing, it could be any of the reasons mentioned above.

currentSuggestions.original: I think that it's on an instinctual level.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: I think that it's on an instinctual level.

currentSuggestions.original: It's a combination of the portrayal and the circumstances.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: It's a combination of the portrayal and the circumstances.

currentSuggestions.original: I know that the very words I'm typing right here are feeling a little weird or cringy to me, because they are coming from my mouth
currentSuggestions.trimmed: I know that the very words I'm typing right here are feeling a little weird or cringy to me, because they are coming from my mouth

ops.insert: It's a combination of the portrayal and the circumstances.

currentSuggestions.original: Cringe!
currentSuggestions.trimmed: Cringe!

currentSuggestions.original: My background as a fan of comedy, has taught me to accept that everyone has their own view on what humor is, and this influences what I laugh
currentSuggestions.trimmed: My background as a fan of comedy, has taught me to accept that everyone has their own view on what humor is, and this influences what I laugh

currentSuggestions.original: The fictitious portrayal of someone like that makes me uncomfortable.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: The fictitious portrayal of someone like that makes me uncomfortable.

currentSuggestions.original: In the end, I'm still able to enjoy comedy television, however I prefer shows that make me think again.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: In the end, I'm still able to enjoy comedy television, however I prefer shows that make me think again.

currentSuggestions.original: I don't find it so easy to laugh at sophomoric and sometimes cruel jokes against people.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: I don't find it so easy to laugh at sophomoric and sometimes cruel jokes against people.

currentSuggestions.original: That has changed the way I look at things.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: That has changed the way I look at things.

currentSuggestions.original: When people are making fun of people I care about, or people who are struggling, that's when the cringe sets in.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: When people are making fun of people I care about, or people who are struggling, that's when the cringe sets in.

currentSuggestions.original: It's also the contrast between the things I was laughing at, a long time ago, and what I think about them today.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: It's also the contrast between the things I was laughing at, a long time ago, and what I think about them today.

currentSuggestions.original: It's all relative.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: It's all relative.

currentSuggestions.original: The result is that it would no longer be funny to me to make light of a person's struggle with weight.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: The result is that it would no longer be funny to me to make light of a person's struggle with weight.

currentSuggestions.original: In my novels, your mileage may vary.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: In my novels, your mileage may vary.

currentSuggestions.original: I was a little disappointed in myself, at first, because I used to laugh at Al Bundy.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: I was a little disappointed in myself, at first, because I used to laugh at Al Bundy.

currentSuggestions.original: "Gremlins 2" is one of my least favorite movies.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: "Gremlins 2" is one of my least favorite movies.

currentSuggestions.original: I've had some real, deep life experiences.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: I've had some real, deep life experiences.
